country.name: Venezuela
country.overview: Venezuela is a country on the northern coast of South America with diverse natural attractions. Along its Caribbean coast are tropical resort islands including Isla de Margarita and the Los Roques archipelago. To the northwest are the Andes Mountains and the colonial town of Mérida, a base for visiting Sierra Nevada National Park. Caracas, the capital, is to the north.

geography.location_description: Northern South America, bordering the Caribbean Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean, between Colombia and Guyana
geography.area_note: almost six times the size of Georgia; slightly more than twice the size of California
geography.climate: tropical; hot, humid; more moderate in highlands
geography.terrain: Andes Mountains and Maracaibo Lowlands in northwest; central plains (llanos); Guiana Highlands in southeast
geography.hazards: subject to floods, rockslides, mudslides; periodic droughts
geography.notes: on major sea and air routes linking North and South America; Angel Falls in the Guiana Highlands is the world's highest waterfall
